# Ruh-Care MVP Development Roadmap

This checklist tracks the ongoing development of the Ruh-Care Version 1 (MVP) application based on the PRD and TRD.

## Phase 1: UI Foundation
- [x] Flutter project initialization
- [x] Splash screen implementation
- [x] Login & Sign Up Screen UI
- [x] App bottom navigation bar & skeleton screens

## Phase 2: Firebase Integration & Setup [x]
- [x] Create Firebase Project (Auth, Firestore, Storage)
- [x] Integrate Firebase SDK into Flutter (`firebase_core`)
- [x] Define Firestore Security Rules based on TRD roles

## Phase 3: Authentication (Logic) [x]
- [x] Implement Firebase Email/Password Authentication
- [x] Create user profile document in Firestore on signup (role: user)
- [x] Implement persistent login state & logout functionality
- [x] Implement role-based routing (Admin vs Doctor vs Patient)

## Phase 4: Patient Features (Discovery & Booking)
- [ ] **Home Screen (Therapies)**: Fetch and display list of therapies from Firestore
- [ ] **Therapy Details**: Show benefits, duration, price, and precautions
- [ ] **Booking Flow - UI**: Date picker and time slot selection
- [ ] **Booking Flow - Logic**: Save appointment to Firestore & handle double-booking prevention

## Phase 5: Patient Features (E-Commerce Store)
- [ ] **Store Screen**: Fetch and display wellness products from Firestore
- [ ] **Product Details**: View product sizes and descriptions
- [ ] **Shopping Cart**: Add items, adjust quantity, calculate total
- [ ] **Checkout Flow**: Place order & save to Firestore

## Phase 6: Admin & Doctor Portals
- [ ] **Doctor Dashboard**: View daily appointment schedule & patient details
- [ ] **Doctor Actions**: Mark appointments as 'completed'
- [ ] **Admin Dashboard**: Overview of all bookings, therapy management
- [ ] **Admin Inventory**: Add/edit products, track clinic supplies

## Phase 7: Polish & Verification
- [ ] Error handling & empty states across the app
- [ ] UI/UX polishing and consistent theming
- [ ] Final manual testing against PRD requirements
